name: Air Transat (ASL Airlines France) 737-73S [C-GTQP] Takeoff from Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
In recent years, Air Transat has leased 737s from European airlines during the winter season for some extra capacity. Normally, the 737-700s skip YYC altogether, operating out of YUL, YYZ, and YVR, but this was a nice surprise! Here we have C-GTQP, leased from ASL Airlines France, taxiing and taking off runway 35L for SJD (Los Cabos). ATC is included, hope you enjoy!

Thanks for watching!
